ciscoSwitchFabricMIB.name: ciscoSwitchFabricMIB

ciscoSwitchFabricMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoSwitchFabricMIB.description: This MIB module defined managed objects that facilitates the management of switching fabric information in a Cisco switch.

CsfFabricLinkType.name: CsfFabricLinkType
CsfFabricLinkType.description: The type of fabric link. other - none of the following qEngineFacingLcXbarLink - queue engine facing linecard crossbar link fabricXbarLink - fabric module crossbar link fabricFacingLcXbarLink - fabric module facing linecard crossbar link lcXbarInterLink - linecard crossbar interlink fabricXbarInterLink - fabric module crossbar interlink centralXbarLink - central fabric link

CsfPercentOrMinusOne.name: CsfPercentOrMinusOne
CsfPercentOrMinusOne.description: An integer that is in the range of a percent value. A value of -1 means that the percentage is not available.

csfFabricUtilTable.name: csfFabricUtilTable
csfFabricUtilTable.description: A table containing fabric utilization information.

csfFabricUtilEntry.name: csfFabricUtilEntry
csfFabricUtilEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the fabric utilization information for a particular type of traffic utilization of a fabric entity. An entry of this table is created if a traffic utilization on a fabric entity is detected by the managed system. An entry of this table is deleted when the removal of fabric entity.

csfFabricUtilLinkType.name: csfFabricUtilLinkType
csfFabricUtilLinkType.description: This object indicates the type of fabric link on which fabric traffic utilization is monitored.

csfFabricUtilIndex.name: csfFabricUtilIndex
csfFabricUtilIndex.description: This object indicates an arbitrary integer value which uniquely identifies the type of traffic utilization.

csfFabricUtilDescr.name: csfFabricUtilDescr
csfFabricUtilDescr.description: This object indicates the human-readable description of the type of fabric traffic utilization.

csfFabricUtilBandwidth.name: csfFabricUtilBandwidth
csfFabricUtilBandwidth.description: This object indicates the bandwidth of the fabric link.

csfFabricUtilIn.name: csfFabricUtilIn
csfFabricUtilIn.description: This object indicates the utilization on the fabric link input.

csfFabricUtilInPeak.name: csfFabricUtilInPeak
csfFabricUtilInPeak.description: This object indicates the peak utilization on the fabric link input.

csfFabricUtilInPeakTime.name: csfFabricUtilInPeakTime
csfFabricUtilInPeakTime.description: This object indicates the time of the most recent change in the corresponding instance value of csfFabricUtilInPeak. This object contains value 0x0000010100000000 when the corresponding instance value of csfFabricUtilInPeak is '0 or '-1'.

csfFabricUtilOut.name: csfFabricUtilOut
csfFabricUtilOut.description: This object indicates the utilization on the fabric link output.

csfFabricUtilOutPeak.name: csfFabricUtilOutPeak
csfFabricUtilOutPeak.description: This object indicates the peak utilization on the fabric link output.

csfFabricUtilOutPeakTime.name: csfFabricUtilOutPeakTime
csfFabricUtilOutPeakTime.description: This object indicates the time of the most recent change in the corresponding instance value of csfFabricUtilOutPeak. This object contains value 0x0000010100000000 when the corresponding instance value of csfFabricUtilInPeak is '0 or '-1'.

csfFabricCrcErrorNotifEnable.name: csfFabricCrcErrorNotifEnable
csfFabricCrcErrorNotifEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates the cfsFabricCrcErrorNotif. A value of 'false' will prevent cfsFabricCrcErrorNotif notifications from being generated by this system.

csfFabricCrcErrorEntPhysicalIndex.name: csfFabricCrcErrorEntPhysicalIndex
csfFabricCrcErrorEntPhysicalIndex.description: This object indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the fabric entity on which fabric CRC error happens.

csfFabricCrcErrorDescr.name: csfFabricCrcErrorDescr
csfFabricCrcErrorDescr.description: This object indicates the fabric CRC error description. A zero-length string indicates that the error description is not available.

csfFabricCrcErrorNotif.name: csfFabricCrcErrorNotif
csfFabricCrcErrorNotif.description: A cfsFabricCrcErrorNotif is generated when fabric CRC errors are detected by the managed system.

csfSwitchFabricMIBCompliance.name: csfSwitchFabricMIBCompliance
csfSwitchFabricMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the CISCO-SWITCH-FABRIC-MIB.

csfSwitchFabricMIBCompliance1.name: csfSwitchFabricMIBCompliance1
csfSwitchFabricMIBCompliance1.description: The compliance statement for the CISCO-SWITCH-FABRIC-MIB.

csfFabricUtilGroup.name: csfFabricUtilGroup
csfFabricUtilGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the information about utilization on the fabric link.

csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsControlGroup.name: csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsControlGroup
csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing notification control for csfFabricCrcErrorNotif.

csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsInfoGroup.name: csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsInfoGroup
csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsInfoGroup.description: A collection of object(s) providing the variable binding for csfFabricCrcErrorNotif.

csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsGroup.name: csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsGroup
csfFabricCrcErrorNotifsGroup.description: A collection of Fabric CRC Error notifications for CISCO-SWITCH-FABRIC-MIB.
